          &lt;div id=&quot;ygrp-text&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;How are the points in the Cantor Set mapped to pitches?
              Are we looking at logarithms of frequencies, frequencies,
              or string length?&lt;br class=&quot;yui-cursor&quot;&gt;
            &lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
            &lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;1) Logarithms of Frequencies (octave):&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;[0&#92;3, 1&#92;3] U [2&#92;3, 3&#92;3]  ===&gt; &lt;br&gt;
            &lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;[0&#92;9, 1&#92;9] U [2&#92;9 3&#92;9] U [6&#92;9, 7&#92;9] U [8&#92;9, 9&#92;9]&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
            &lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;2) Frequencies:&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;[3/3, 4/3] U [5/3, 6/3]&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;[9/9, 10/9] U [11/9, 12/9] U [15/9, 16/9] U [17/9, 18/9]&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
            &lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;3) String Length:&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;[3/6, 3/5] U [3/4, 3/3]&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;[9/18, 9/17] U [9/16, 9/15] U [9/12, 9/11] U [9/10, 9/9]&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;


